---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = 'March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — T1V App" description="Privacy policy for the T1V App by Turn1Visuals.">

  <section class="privacy-section">
    <div class="container privacy-inner">

      <header class="privacy-header">
        <p class="section-label">T1V App</p>
        <h1 class="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="privacy-meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how the T1V App ("the App"), developed by Turn1Visuals, handles
          data when you use it. The App is a personal-use Electron desktop application for managing
          Formula 1 content and live streams.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>
          The T1V App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data to servers operated by
          Turn1Visuals. There are no analytics, telemetry, crash reports, or usage tracking of any kind
          built into the App.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Data Stored Locally</h2>
        <p>
          The App stores the following data locally on your device only, in the application data directory
          (<code>%APPDATA%/t1v-app/</code> on Windows):
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>OAuth access tokens and refresh tokens for connected platforms (TikTok, YouTube, Twitch)</li>
          <li>API client credentials entered in Settings (Client ID, Client Secret)</li>
          <li>App configuration such as OBS settings, browser tabs, and launcher shortcuts</li>
          <li>Stream setup fields (title, description, category) saved in browser localStorage</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data never leaves your device except when used directly to communicate with the
          respective platform APIs on your behalf.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Platform Integrations</h2>
        <p>
          The App connects to the following third-party platforms using their official APIs.
          Each platform's own privacy policy applies to data processed on their side:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/page/global/privacy-policy/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TikTok Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google / YouTube Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.twitch.tv/p/legal/privacy-notice/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitch Privacy Notice</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Authentication with these platforms is handled via OAuth 2.0. The App only requests the
          permissions necessary for its features (uploading videos, managing streams, sending chat messages).
        </p>

        <h2>4. OBS Integration</h2>
        <p>
          The App communicates with OBS Studio running locally on the same machine via the OBS WebSocket
          protocol. No OBS data is transmitted externally.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Webviews</h2>
        <p>
          The App displays webviews for platform dashboards (e.g. YouTube Studio, Twitch Stream Manager,
          Twitter/X Producer). These load external websites directly in the App using isolated browser
          sessions. The respective platform's privacy policies apply to these sessions.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The App is not intended for use by anyone under the age of 13. It does not knowingly collect
          data from children.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated when new features or integrations are added. The date at the top
          of this page reflects the most recent revision.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about this Privacy Policy, contact Turn1Visuals at
          <a href="mailto:info@turn1visuals.com">info@turn1visuals.com</a>.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
  }

  .privacy-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .privacy-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .privacy-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-block: 0.75rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .privacy-meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .prose {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .prose h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: none;
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .prose ul li {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .prose ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose code {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    background: var(--color-surface, #111);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
</style>
